Question 6.2.1:

Function: sum_0_M [f(x)]

Constraint x_i in the set X, for i=0,1,...,m

The dual problem is:

	Lagrangian: L(x,lambda) = sum_0_M[f(x)] + sum_0_M[lambda_i*x_i]

        Minimal Lagrangian: argmin{L(x,lambda)} = argmin {sum_0_M[f(x)] + sum_0_M[lambda*x]}

                                                = 0

        Dual: q(lambda) = sum_0_M[q(lambda_i)]

        Minimal Dual: argmin{q(lambda)} = argmin{sum_0_M[q(lambda_i)]}

                                        = argmin{q(lambda_0) + sum_1_M[q(lambda_i)]}

                                        = 0
        Dual Problem: maximize q(lambda_0) + sum_1_M[q(lambda_i)]

                      constraint: lambda_i

The optimal solution for the primal is (x*,lambda*) and also for the dual problem.


